<li id="cite_note-51"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-51">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Cartwright, Nancy (1983), <i>How the Laws of Physics Lie</i>. Oxford: Oxford University Press. <a href="Special_BookSources/0198247044" class="internal mw-magiclink-isbn">ISBN 0-19-824704-4</a></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-52"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-52">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Andreas Vesalius, <i>Epistola, Rationem, Modumque Propinandi Radicis Chynae Decocti</i> (1546), 141. Quoted and translated in C.D. O'Malley, <i>Andreas Vesalius of Brussels</i>, (1964), 116. As quoted by <a href="#CITEREFBynumPorter2005">Bynum &amp; Porter 2005</a>, p.&#160;597: Andreas Vesalius,597#1.</span></li>
