<li><span class="citation" id="CITEREFFranklin2009"><a href="James_Franklin_(philosopher)" title="James Franklin (philosopher)">Franklin, James</a> (2009), <i>What Science Knows: And How It Knows It</i>, New York: Encounter Books, <a href="International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="Special_BookSources/1-59403-207-6" title="Special:BookSources/1-59403-207-6">1-59403-207-6</a></span>.</li>
<li><a href="Hans-Georg_Gadamer" title="Hans-Georg Gadamer">Gadamer, Hans-Georg</a>, <i>Reason in the Age of Science</i>, Frederick G. Lawrence (trans.), MIT Press, Cambridge, MA, 1981.</li>
<li><a href="../Ronald_N._Giere" title="Ronald N. Giere" class="mw-redirect">Giere, Ronald N.</a> (ed.), <i>Cognitive Models of Science</i>, vol. 15 in 'Minnesota Studies in the Philosophy of Science', University of Minnesota Press, Minneapolis, MN, 1992.</li>
